Patch Set 1:

@samuli: 3. is about the fact, that without any argument it will rely on that there is already a passwordless login - some ssh key is already in the place - and it will just generate another key and distribute it too - redundant

I really tried to find a good place for this playbook, but either you will use passwords with it and it will deploy a ssh key or you dont use it at all - I dont think that it belongs here, because it tries to solve chicken-egg problem or it is the only playbook which may require interactivity from the user - other are just batch jobs and they will run, fail or succeed
